constructors.name: user
constructors.description: Indicates info about a certain user.

fields.name: self
fields.description: Whether this user indicates the currently logged in user

fields.name: contact
fields.description: Whether this user is a contact When updating the local peer database , do not apply changes to this field if the min flag is set.

fields.name: mutual_contact
fields.description: Whether this user is a mutual contact. When updating the local peer database , do not apply changes to this field if the min flag is set.

fields.name: deleted
fields.description: Whether the account of this user was deleted. Changes to this flag should invalidate the local userFull cache for this user ID, see here » for more info.

fields.name: bot
fields.description: Is this user a bot? Changes to this flag should invalidate the local userFull cache for this user ID, see here » for more info.

fields.name: bot_chat_history
fields.description: Can the bot see all messages in groups?

fields.name: bot_nochats
fields.description: Can the bot be added to groups?

fields.name: restricted
fields.description: Access to this user must be restricted for the reason specified in restriction_reason

fields.name: bot_inline_geo
fields.description: Whether the bot can request our geolocation in inline mode

fields.name: support
fields.description: Whether this is an official support user

fields.name: scam
fields.description: This may be a scam user

fields.name: apply_min_photo
fields.description: If set and min is set, the value of photo can be used to update the local database, see the documentation of that flag for more info.

fields.name: fake
fields.description: If set, this user was reported by many users as a fake or scam user: be careful when interacting with them.

fields.name: bot_attach_menu
fields.description: Whether this bot offers an attachment menu web app

fields.name: premium
fields.description: Whether this user is a Telegram Premium user Changes to this flag should invalidate the local userFull cache for this user ID, see here » for more info. Changes to this flag if the self flag is set should also trigger the following calls, to refresh the respective caches: - The help.getConfig cache - The messages.getTopReactions cache if the bot flag is not set

fields.name: attach_menu_enabled
fields.description: Whether we installed the attachment menu web app offered by this bot. When updating the local peer database , do not apply changes to this field if the min flag is set.

fields.name: bot_can_edit
fields.description: Whether we can edit the profile picture, name, about text and description of this bot because we own it. When updating the local peer database , do not apply changes to this field if the min flag is set. Changes to this flag (if min is not set) should invalidate the local userFull cache for this user ID.

fields.name: close_friend
fields.description: Whether we marked this user as a close friend, see here » for more info . When updating the local peer database , do not apply changes to this field if the min flag is set.

fields.name: stories_hidden
fields.description: Whether we have hidden » all active stories of this user. When updating the local peer database , do not apply changes to this field if the min flag is set.

fields.name: stories_unavailable
fields.description: No stories from this user are visible.

fields.name: contact_require_premium
fields.description: See here for more info on this flag » .

fields.name: bot_business
fields.description: Whether this bot can be connected to a user as specified here » .

fields.name: bot_has_main_app
fields.description: If set, this bot has configured a Main Mini App » .

fields.name: id
fields.description: ID of the user, see here » for more info and the available ID range.

fields.name: access_hash
fields.description: Access hash of the user, see here » for more info. If this flag is set, when updating the local peer database , generate a virtual flag called min_access_hash , which is: - Set to true if min is set AND -- The phone flag is not set OR -- The phone flag is set and the associated phone number string is non-empty - Set to false otherwise. Then, apply both access_hash and min_access_hash to the local database if: - min_access_hash is false OR - min_access_hash is true AND -- There is no locally cached object for this user OR -- There is no access_hash in the local cache OR -- The cached object's min_access_hash is also true If the final merged object stored to the database has the min_access_hash field set to true, the related access_hash is only suitable to use in inputPeerPhotoFileLocation » , to directly download the profile pictures of users, everywhere else a inputPeer*FromMessage constructor will have to be generated as specified here » . Bots can also use min access hashes in some conditions, by passing 0 instead of the min access hash.

fields.name: first_name
fields.description: First name. When updating the local peer database , apply changes to this field only if: - The min flag is not set OR - The min flag is set AND -- The min flag of the locally cached user entry is set.

fields.name: last_name
fields.description: Last name. When updating the local peer database , apply changes to this field only if: - The min flag is not set OR - The min flag is set AND -- The min flag of the locally cached user entry is set.

fields.name: username
fields.description: Main active username. When updating the local peer database , apply changes to this field only if: - The min flag is not set OR - The min flag is set AND -- The min flag of the locally cached user entry is set. Changes to this flag should invalidate the local userFull cache for this user ID if the above conditions are respected and the bot_can_edit flag is also set.

fields.name: phone
fields.description: Phone number. When updating the local peer database , apply changes to this field only if: - The min flag is not set OR - The min flag is set AND -- The min flag of the locally cached user entry is set.

fields.name: photo
fields.description: Profile picture of user. When updating the local peer database , apply changes to this field only if: - The min flag is not set OR - The min flag is set AND -- The apply_min_photo flag is set OR -- The min flag of the locally cached user entry is set.

fields.name: status
fields.description: Online status of user. When updating the local peer database , apply changes to this field only if: - The min flag is not set OR - The min flag is set AND -- The min flag of the locally cached user entry is set OR -- The locally cached user entry is equal to userStatusEmpty .

fields.name: bot_info_version
fields.description: Version of the bot_info field in userFull , incremented every time it changes. Changes to this flag should invalidate the local userFull cache for this user ID, see here » for more info.

fields.name: restriction_reason
fields.description: Contains the reason why access to this user must be restricted.

fields.name: bot_inline_placeholder
fields.description: Inline placeholder for this inline bot

fields.name: usernames
fields.description: Additional usernames. When updating the local peer database , apply changes to this field only if: - The min flag is not set OR - The min flag is set AND -- The min flag of the locally cached user entry is set. Changes to this flag (if the above conditions are respected) should invalidate the local userFull cache for this user ID.

fields.name: stories_max_id
fields.description: ID of the maximum read story . When updating the local peer database , do not apply changes to this field if the min flag of the incoming constructor is set.

fields.name: bot_active_users
fields.description: Monthly Active Users (MAU) of this bot (may be absent for small bots).

fields.name: send_paid_messages_stars
fields.description: If set, the user has enabled paid messages » , we might need to pay the specified amount of Stars to send them messages, depending on the configured exceptions: check userFull . send_paid_messages_stars or users.getRequirementsToContact to see if the currently logged in user actually has to pay or not, see here » for the full flow.

constructors.name: channel

fields.name: creator
fields.description: Whether the current user is the creator of this channel

fields.name: left
fields.description: Whether the current user has left or is not a member of this channel

fields.name: verified
fields.description: Is this channel verified by telegram?

fields.name: megagroup
fields.description: Is this a supergroup? Changes to this flag should invalidate the local channelFull cache for this channel/supergroup ID, see here » for more info.

fields.name: restricted
fields.description: Whether viewing/writing in this channel for a reason (see restriction_reason )

fields.name: scam
fields.description: This channel/supergroup is probably a scam Changes to this flag should invalidate the local channelFull cache for this channel/supergroup ID, see here » for more info.

fields.name: has_link
fields.description: Whether this channel has a linked discussion group » (or this supergroup is a channel's discussion group). The actual ID of the linked channel/supergroup is contained in channelFull . linked_chat_id . Changes to this flag should invalidate the local channelFull cache for this channel/supergroup ID, see here » for more info.

fields.name: has_geo
fields.description: Whether this chanel has a geoposition

fields.name: slowmode_enabled
fields.description: Whether slow mode is enabled for groups to prevent flood in chat. Changes to this flag should invalidate the local channelFull cache for this channel/supergroup ID, see here » for more info.

fields.name: call_active
fields.description: Whether a group call or livestream is currently active

fields.name: call_not_empty
fields.description: Whether there's anyone in the group call or livestream

fields.name: fake
fields.description: If set, this supergroup/channel was reported by many users as a fake or scam: be careful when interacting with it. Changes to this flag should invalidate the local channelFull cache for this channel/supergroup ID, see here » for more info.

fields.name: gigagroup
fields.description: Whether this supergroup is a gigagroup Changes to this flag should invalidate the local channelFull cache for this channel/supergroup ID, see here » for more info.

fields.name: noforwards
fields.description: Whether this channel or group is protected , thus does not allow forwarding messages from it

fields.name: join_to_send
fields.description: Whether a user needs to join the supergroup before they can send messages: can be false only for discussion groups » , toggle using channels.toggleJoinToSend Changes to this flag should invalidate the local channelFull cache for this channel/supergroup ID, see here » for more info.

fields.name: join_request
fields.description: Whether a user's join request will have to be approved by administrators , toggle using channels.toggleJoinToSend Changes to this flag should invalidate the local channelFull cache for this channel/supergroup ID, see here » for more info.

fields.name: forum
fields.description: Whether this supergroup is a forum . Changes to this flag should invalidate the local channelFull cache for this channel/supergroup ID, see here » for more info.

fields.name: stories_hidden
fields.description: Whether we have hidden all stories posted by this channel » .

fields.name: stories_hidden_min
fields.description: If set, indicates that the stories_hidden flag was not populated, and its value must cannot be relied on; use the previously cached value, or re-fetch the constructor using channels.getChannels to obtain the latest value of the stories_hidden flag.

fields.name: stories_unavailable
fields.description: No stories from the channel are visible.

fields.name: signature_profiles
fields.description: If set, messages sent by admins to this channel will link to the admin's profile (just like with groups).

fields.name: autotranslation
fields.description: If set, autotranslation was enabled for all users by the admin of the channel, as specified here » .

fields.name: broadcast_messages_allowed
fields.description: If set, this channel has an associated monoforum » , and its ID is specified in the linked_monoforum_id flag.

fields.name: monoforum
fields.description: If set, this is a monoforum » , and the ID of the associated channel is specified in the linked_monoforum_id .

fields.name: forum_tabs
fields.description: If set, enables the tabbed forum UI » .

fields.name: id
fields.description: ID of the channel, see here » for more info and the available ID range.

fields.name: access_hash
fields.description: Access hash, see here » for more info

fields.name: date
fields.description: Date when the user joined the supergroup/channel, or if the user isn't a member, its creation date

fields.name: restriction_reason
fields.description: Contains the reason why access to this channel must be restricted. Changes to this flag should invalidate the local channelFull cache for this channel/supergroup ID, see here » for more info.

fields.name: admin_rights
fields.description: Admin rights of the user in this channel (see rights )

fields.name: banned_rights
fields.description: Banned rights of the user in this channel (see rights )

fields.name: stories_max_id
fields.description: ID of the maximum read story .

fields.name: level
fields.description: Boost level . Changes to this flag should invalidate the local channelFull cache for this channel/supergroup ID, see here » for more info.

fields.name: subscription_until_date
fields.description: Expiration date of the Telegram Star subscription » the current user has bought to gain access to this channel.

fields.name: send_paid_messages_stars
fields.description: If set, this supergroup or monoforum has enabled paid messages » , we might need to pay the specified amount of Stars to send messages to it, depending on the configured exceptions: check channelFull . send_paid_messages_stars to see if the currently logged in user actually has to pay or not, see here » for the full flow (only set for the monoforum, not the associated channel).

fields.name: linked_monoforum_id
fields.description: For channels with associated monoforums , the monoforum ID. For Monoforums , the ID of the associated channel.

fields.name: stargifts_count

fields.name: send_paid_messages_stars
fields.description: If set and bigger than 0, this supergroup, monoforum or the monoforum associated to this channel has enabled paid messages » and we must pay the specified amount of Stars to send messages to it, see here » for the full flow. This flag will be set both for the monoforum and for channelFull of the associated channel). If set and equal to 0, the monoforum requires payment in general but we were exempted from paying.

fields.name: main_tab
fields.description: The main tab for the channel's profile, see here » for more info.

constructors.name: message
constructors.description: A message

fields.name: mentioned
fields.description: Whether we were mentioned in this message

fields.name: media_unread
fields.description: Whether there are unread media attachments in this message

fields.name: silent
fields.description: Whether this is a silent message (no notification triggered)

fields.name: post
fields.description: Whether this is a channel post

fields.name: from_scheduled
fields.description: Whether this is a scheduled message

fields.name: legacy
fields.description: This is a legacy message: it has to be refetched with the new layer

fields.name: edit_hide
fields.description: Whether the message should be shown as not modified to the user, even if an edit date is present

fields.name: noforwards
fields.description: Whether this message is protected and thus cannot be forwarded; clients should also prevent users from saving attached media (i.e. videos should only be streamed, photos should be kept in RAM, et cetera).

fields.name: invert_media
fields.description: If set, any eventual webpage preview will be shown on top of the message instead of at the bottom.

fields.name: offline
fields.description: If set, the message was sent because of a scheduled action by the message sender, for example, as away, or a greeting service message.

fields.name: video_processing_pending
fields.description: The video contained in the message is currently being processed by the server (i.e. to generate alternative qualities, that will be contained in the final messageMediaDocument . alt_document ), and will be sent once the video is processed, which will happen approximately at the specified date (i.e. messages with this flag set should be treated similarly to scheduled messages , but instead of the scheduled date, date contains the estimated conversion date). See here » for more info.

fields.name: paid_suggested_post_stars
fields.description: Set if this is a suggested channel post » that was paid using Telegram Stars .

fields.name: paid_suggested_post_ton
fields.description: Set if this is a suggested channel post » that was paid using Toncoins.

fields.name: from_id
fields.description: ID of the sender of the message

fields.name: from_boosts_applied
fields.description: Supergroups only, contains the number of boosts this user has given the current supergroup, and should be shown in the UI in the header of the message. Only present for incoming messages from non-anonymous supergroup members that have boosted the supergroup. Note that this counter should be locally overridden for non-anonymous outgoing messages, according to the current value of channelFull . boosts_applied , to ensure the value is correct even for messages sent by the current user before a supergroup was boosted (or after a boost has expired or the number of boosts has changed); do not update this value for incoming messages from other users, even if their boosts have changed.

fields.name: peer_id
fields.description: Peer ID, the chat where this message was sent

fields.name: saved_peer_id
fields.description: Messages from a saved messages dialog » will have peer = inputPeerSelf and the saved_peer_id flag set to the ID of the saved dialog. Messages from a monoforum » will have peer =ID of the monoforum and the saved_peer_id flag set to the ID of a topic.

fields.name: via_bot_id
fields.description: ID of the inline bot that generated the message

fields.name: via_business_bot_id
fields.description: Whether the message was sent by the business bot specified in via_bot_id on behalf of the user.

fields.name: replies
fields.description: Info about post comments (for channels) or message replies (for groups)

fields.name: edit_date
fields.description: Last edit date of this message

fields.name: post_author
fields.description: Name of the author of this message for channel posts (with signatures enabled)

fields.name: grouped_id
fields.description: Multiple media messages sent using messages.sendMultiMedia with the same grouped ID indicate an album or media group

fields.name: restriction_reason
fields.description: Contains the reason why access to this message must be restricted.

fields.name: ttl_period
fields.description: Time To Live of the message, once message.date+message.ttl_period === time(), the message will be deleted on the server, and must be deleted locally as well.

fields.name: quick_reply_shortcut_id
fields.description: If set, this message is a quick reply shortcut message » (note that quick reply shortcut messages sent to a private chat will not have this field set).

fields.name: effect
fields.description: A message effect that should be played as specified here » .

fields.name: report_delivery_until_date
fields.description: Used for Telegram Gateway verification messages : if set and the current unixtime is bigger than the specified unixtime, invoke messages.reportMessagesDelivery passing the ID and the peer of this message as soon as it is received by the client (optionally batching requests for the same peer).

fields.name: paid_message_stars
fields.description: The amount of stars the sender has paid to send the message, see here » for more info.

fields.description: Maximum allowed incoming ring time in VoIP calls: if the current user doesn't reply within the specified time (in milliseconds), the call will be automatically refused

fields.name: call_connect_timeout_ms
fields.description: VoIP connection timeout: if the instance of libtgvoip on the other side of the call doesn't connect to our instance of libtgvoip within the specified time (in milliseconds), the call must be aborted

fields.name: call_packet_timeout_ms
fields.description: If during a VoIP call a packet isn't received for the specified period of time, the call must be aborted

constructors.name: keyboardButtonUrlAuth
constructors.description: Button to request a user to authorize via URL using Seamless Telegram Login . When the user clicks on such a button, messages.requestUrlAuth should be called, providing the button_id and the ID of the container message. The returned urlAuthResultRequest object will contain more details about the authorization request ( request_write_access if the bot would like to send messages to the user along with the username of the bot which will be used for user authorization). Finally, the user can choose to call messages.acceptUrlAuth to get a urlAuthResultAccepted with the URL to open instead of the url of this constructor, or a urlAuthResultDefault , in which case the url of this constructor must be opened, instead. If the user refuses the authorization request but still wants to open the link, the url of this constructor must be used.

fields.name: fwd_text
fields.description: New text of the button in forwarded messages.

fields.name: url
fields.description: An HTTP URL to be opened with user authorization data added to the query string when the button is pressed. If the user refuses to provide authorization data, the original URL without information about the user will be opened. The data added is the same as described in Receiving authorization data . NOTE : Services must always check the hash of the received data to verify the authentication and the integrity of the data as described in Checking authorization .

fields.name: button_id
fields.description: ID of the button to pass to messages.requestUrlAuth

constructors.name: replyKeyboardForceReply
constructors.description: Force the user to send a reply

fields.name: single_use
fields.description: Requests clients to hide the keyboard as soon as it's been used. The keyboard will still be available, but clients will automatically display the usual letter-keyboard in the chat – the user can press a special button in the input field to see the custom keyboard again.

fields.name: selective
fields.description: Use this parameter if you want to show the keyboard to specific users only. Targets: 1) users that are @mentioned in the text of the Message object; 2) if the bot's message is a reply (has reply_to_message_id), sender of the original message. Example: A user requests to change the bot's language, bot replies to the request with a keyboard to select the new language. Other users in the group don't see the keyboard.

fields.name: placeholder
fields.description: The placeholder to be shown in the input field when the keyboard is active; 1-64 characters.

constructors.name: replyKeyboardHide
constructors.description: Hide sent bot keyboard

fields.name: selective
fields.description: Use this flag if you want to remove the keyboard for specific users only. Targets: 1) users that are @mentioned in the text of the Message object; 2) if the bot's message is a reply (has reply_to_message_id), sender of the original message. Example: A user votes in a poll, bot returns confirmation message in reply to the vote and removes the keyboard for that user, while still showing the keyboard with poll options to users who haven't voted yet

fields.name: resize
fields.description: Requests clients to resize the keyboard vertically for optimal fit (e.g., make the keyboard smaller if there are just two rows of buttons). If not set, the custom keyboard is always of the same height as the app's standard keyboard.

fields.name: single_use
fields.description: Requests clients to hide the keyboard as soon as it's been used. The keyboard will still be available, but clients will automatically display the usual letter-keyboard in the chat – the user can press a special button in the input field to see the custom keyboard again.

fields.name: selective
fields.description: Use this parameter if you want to show the keyboard to specific users only. Targets: 1) users that are @mentioned in the text of the Message object; 2) if the bot's message is a reply (has reply_to_message_id), sender of the original message. Example: A user requests to change the bot's language, bot replies to the request with a keyboard to select the new language. Other users in the group don't see the keyboard.

fields.name: persistent
fields.description: Requests clients to always show the keyboard when the regular keyboard is hidden.

fields.name: placeholder
fields.description: The placeholder to be shown in the input field when the keyboard is active; 1-64 characters.

constructors.name: messageFwdHeader
constructors.description: Info about a forwarded message

fields.name: imported
fields.description: Whether this message was imported from a foreign chat service, click here for more info »

fields.name: saved_out
fields.description: Only for messages forwarded to saved messages » , set if the original message was outgoing (though the message may have been originally outgoing even if this flag is not set, if from_id points to the current user).

fields.name: from_id
fields.description: The ID of the user that originally sent the message

fields.name: from_name
fields.description: The name of the user that originally sent the message

fields.name: date
fields.description: When was the message originally sent

fields.name: channel_post
fields.description: ID of the channel message that was forwarded

fields.name: post_author
fields.description: For channels and if signatures are enabled, author of the channel message

fields.name: saved_from_peer
fields.description: Only for messages forwarded to saved messages » , contains the dialog where the message was originally sent.

fields.name: saved_from_msg_id
fields.description: Only for messages forwarded to saved messages » , contains the original ID of the message in saved_from_peer .

fields.name: saved_from_id
fields.description: Only for forwarded messages reforwarded to saved messages » , contains the sender of the original message (i.e. if user A sends a message, then user B forwards it somewhere, then user C saves it to saved messages, this field will contain the ID of user B and from_id will contain the ID of user A).

fields.name: saved_from_name
fields.description: Only for forwarded messages from users with forward privacy enabled, sent by users with forward privacy enabled, reforwarded to saved messages » , contains the sender of the original message (i.e. if user A (fwd privacy enabled) sends a message, then user B (fwd privacy enabled) forwards it somewhere, then user C saves it to saved messages, this field will contain the name of user B and from_name will contain the name of user A).

fields.name: saved_date
fields.description: Only for forwarded messages reforwarded to saved messages » , indicates when was the original message sent (i.e. if user A sends a message @ unixtime 1, then user B forwards it somewhere @ unixtime 2, then user C saves it to saved messages @ unixtime 3, this field will contain 2, date will contain 1 and the date of the containing message will contain 3).

constructors.raw_tl: messageFwdHeader#4e4df4bb flags:# imported:flags.7?true saved_out:flags.11?true from_id:flags.0?Peer from_name:flags.5?string date:int channel_post:flags.2?int post_author:flags.3?string saved_from_peer:flags.4?Peer saved_from_msg_id:flags.4?int saved_from_id:flags.8?Peer saved_from_name:flags.9?string saved_date:flags.10?int psa_type:flags.6?string = MessageFwdHeader;

fields.name: archive_and_mute_new_noncontact_peers
fields.description: Whether to archive and mute new chats from non-contacts

fields.description: Whether unmuted chats will be kept in the Archive chat list when they get a new message.

fields.description: Whether unmuted chats that are always included or pinned in a folder , will be kept in the Archive chat list when they get a new message. Ignored if keep_archived_unmuted is set.

fields.name: hide_read_marks
fields.description: If this flag is set, the inputPrivacyKeyStatusTimestamp key will also apply to the ability to use messages.getOutboxReadDate on messages sent to us. Meaning, users that cannot see our exact last online date due to the current value of the inputPrivacyKeyStatusTimestamp key will receive a 403 USER_PRIVACY_RESTRICTED error when invoking messages.getOutboxReadDate to fetch the exact read date of a message they sent to us. The userFull . read_dates_private flag will be set for users that have this flag enabled.

fields.name: new_noncontact_peers_require_premium
fields.description: See here for more info on this flag » .

fields.name: display_gifts_button
fields.description: Enables or disables our userFull . display_gifts_button flag: if the userFull . display_gifts_button flag of both us and another user is set, a gift button should always be displayed in the text field in private chats with the other user: once clicked, the gift UI should be displayed, offering the user options to gift Telegram Premium » subscriptions or Telegram Gifts » .

fields.name: noncontact_peers_paid_stars
fields.description: If configured, specifies the number of stars users must pay us to send us a message, see here » for more info on paid messages.

fields.name: disallowed_gifts
fields.description: Disallows the reception of specific gift types.

fields.name: reply_to_msg_id
fields.description: The message ID to reply to.

fields.description: This field must contain the topic ID only when replying to messages in forum topics different from the "General" topic (i.e. reply_to_msg_id is set and reply_to_msg_id != topicID and topicID != 1 ). If the replied-to message is deleted before the method finishes execution, the value in this field will be used to send the message to the correct topic, instead of the "General" topic.

fields.name: quote_offset
fields.description: Offset of the message quote_text within the original message (in UTF-16 code units ).

fields.name: monoforum_peer_id
fields.description: Must be set to the ID of the topic when replying to a message within a monoforum topic .

fields.name: todo_item_id
fields.description: Can be set to reply to the specified item of a todo list » .

constructors.name: starsTransaction
constructors.description: Represents a Telegram Stars or TON transaction » .

fields.name: refund
fields.description: Whether this transaction is a refund.

fields.name: gift
fields.description: This transaction was a gift from the user in peer.peer .

fields.name: reaction
fields.description: This transaction is a paid reaction » .

fields.name: stargift_upgrade
fields.description: This transaction pays for the upgrade of a gift to a collectible gift » .

fields.name: business_transfer
fields.description: This transaction transfers stars from the balance of a user account connected to a business bot , to the balance of the business bot, see here » for more info.

fields.name: stargift_resale
fields.description: This transaction is related to the resale of a collectible gift » .

fields.name: posts_search
fields.description: Represents payment for a paid global post search » .

fields.name: stargift_prepaid_upgrade
fields.description: Represents payment for a separate prepaid upgrade of a gift .

fields.name: amount
fields.description: Amount of Telegram Stars or TON.

fields.name: peer
fields.description: Source of the incoming transaction, or its recipient for outgoing transactions.

fields.name: title
fields.description: For transactions with bots, title of the bought product.

fields.name: description
fields.description: For transactions with bots, description of the bought product.

fields.name: photo
fields.description: For transactions with bots, photo of the bought product.

fields.name: transaction_date
fields.description: If neither pending nor failed are set, the transaction was completed successfully, and this field will contain the point in time (Unix timestamp) when the withdrawal was completed successfully.

fields.name: transaction_url
fields.description: If neither pending nor failed are set, the transaction was completed successfully, and this field will contain a URL where the withdrawal transaction can be viewed.

fields.name: bot_payload
fields.description: Bot specified invoice payload (i.e. the payload passed to inputMediaInvoice when creating the invoice ).

fields.name: msg_id
fields.description: For paid media transactions » , message ID of the paid media posted to peer.peer (can point to a deleted message; either way, extended_media will always contain the bought media).

fields.name: subscription_period
fields.description: The number of seconds between consecutive Telegram Star debiting for Telegram Star subscriptions » .

fields.name: giveaway_post_id
fields.description: ID of the message containing the messageMediaGiveaway , for incoming star giveaway prizes .

fields.name: stargift
fields.description: This transaction indicates a purchase or a sale (conversion back to Stars) of a gift » .

fields.name: floodskip_number
fields.description: This transaction is payment for paid bot broadcasts . Paid broadcasts are only allowed if the allow_paid_floodskip parameter of messages.sendMessage and other message sending methods is set while trying to broadcast more than 30 messages per second to bot users. The integer value returned by this flag indicates the number of billed API calls.

fields.name: starref_commission_permille
fields.description: This transaction is the receival (or refund) of an affiliate commission (i.e. this is the transaction received by the peer that created the referral link , flag 17 is for transactions made by users that imported the referral link).

fields.name: starref_peer
fields.description: For transactions made by referred users , the peer that received the affiliate commission.

fields.name: starref_amount
fields.description: For transactions made by referred users , the amount of Telegram Stars received by the affiliate, can be negative for refunds.

fields.name: paid_messages
fields.description: This transaction is related to the reception or transmission of a paid message » .

fields.name: premium_gift_months
fields.description: This transaction indicates the payment for a gifted Telegram Premium subscription » .

fields.name: ads_proceeds_from_date
fields.description: Indicates that this is payment for ad revenue from the specified unixtime (always set together with ads_proceeds_to_date ).

fields.name: ads_proceeds_to_date
fields.description: Indicates that this is payment for ad revenue to the specified unixtime.

constructors.raw_tl: starsTransaction#13659eb0 flags:# refund:flags.3?true pending:flags.4?true failed:flags.6?true gift:flags.10?true reaction:flags.11?true stargift_upgrade:flags.18?true business_transfer:flags.21?true stargift_resale:flags.22?true posts_search:flags.24?true stargift_prepaid_upgrade:flags.25?true id:string amount:StarsAmount date:int peer:StarsTransactionPeer title:flags.0?string description:flags.1?string photo:flags.2?WebDocument transaction_date:flags.5?int transaction_url:flags.5?string bot_payload:flags.7?bytes msg_id:flags.8?int extended_media:flags.9?Vector<MessageMedia> subscription_period:flags.12?int giveaway_post_id:flags.13?int stargift:flags.14?StarGift floodskip_number:flags.15?int starref_commission_permille:flags.16?int starref_peer:flags.17?Peer starref_amount:flags.17?StarsAmount paid_messages:flags.19?int premium_gift_months:flags.20?int ads_proceeds_from_date:flags.23?int ads_proceeds_to_date:flags.23?int = StarsTransaction;

methods.name: account.getBotBusinessConnection
methods.description: Bots may invoke this method to re-fetch the updateBotBusinessConnect constructor associated with a specific business connection_id , see here » for more info on connected business bots. This is needed for example for freshly logged in bots that are receiving some updateBotNewBusinessMessage , etc. updates because some users have already connected to the bot before it could login. In this case, the bot is receiving messages from the business connection, but it hasn't cached the associated updateBotBusinessConnect with info about the connection (can it reply to messages? etc.) yet, and cannot receive the old ones because they were sent when the bot wasn't logged into the session yet. This method can be used to fetch info about a not-yet-cached business connection, and should not be invoked if the info is already cached or to fetch changes, as eventual changes will automatically be sent as new updateBotBusinessConnect updates to the bot using the usual update delivery methods » .

methods.name: stories.sendStory
methods.description: Uploads a Telegram Story .

fields.name: pinned
fields.description: Whether to add the story to the profile automatically upon expiration. If not set, the story will only be added to the archive, see here » for more info.

fields.description: If set, disables forwards, screenshots, and downloads.

fields.description: Unique client message ID required to prevent message resending.
